cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.SI

The paper proposes a new method for multi-instance learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The method involves treating instances in a bag as non-i.i.d. samples, which suggests a focus on learning from structured data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of graphs and kernels also suggests a possible fit with cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
